.TH "calipso_pad_write" 9 "calipso_pad_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calipso_pad_write \- Writes pad bytes in TLV format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" calipso_pad_write
.BI "(unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer
.IP "offset" 12
offset from start of buffer to write padding
.IP "count" 12
number of pad bytes to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write \fIcount\fP bytes of TLV padding into \fIbuffer\fP starting at offset \fIoffset\fP.
\fIcount\fP should be less than 8 - see RFC 4942.
